title: Apply to tax a Heavy Goods Vehicle (HGV)

heading_context: Apply to tax a Heavy Goods Vehicle (HGV)
chunks.html_content: Fill in form V85 and apply in person at a Post Office that deals with vehicle tax.
chunks.plain_content:
Apply to tax a Heavy Goods Vehicle (HGV)
Fill in form V85 and apply in person at a Post Office that deals with vehicle tax.

heading_context: Apply to tax a Heavy Goods Vehicle (HGV)
chunks.html_content: You need HGV tax for lorries that weigh more than 3.5 tonnes when loaded.
chunks.plain_content:
Apply to tax a Heavy Goods Vehicle (HGV)
You need HGV tax for lorries that weigh more than 3.5 tonnes when loaded.

heading_context: Apply to tax a Heavy Goods Vehicle (HGV)
chunks.html_content:
You need to take the vehicle log book (V5C). You can apply for a replacement if you do not have one.

This guide is also available in Welsh (Cymraeg).

The amount of tax you need to pay depends on your vehicles tax band and whether it has road-friendly suspension.
chunks.plain_content:
Apply to tax a Heavy Goods Vehicle (HGV)
Tax rates for HGVs

You need to take the vehicle log book (V5C). You can apply for a replacement if you do not have one.
This guide is also available in Welsh (Cymraeg).
The amount of tax you need to pay depends on your vehicles tax band and whether it has road-friendly suspension.
